,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 1221/97 of 25 June 1997 laying down general rules for the application of measures to improve the production and marketing of honey (1), and in particular Article 5 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 2300/97 (2), as amended by Commission Regulation (EC) No 758/98 (3), lays down provisions for the implementation of measures to improve the production and the marketing of honey;
Whereas that amendment also brought forward the date for notification of programmes; whereas, as a result, the date of the agricultural conversion rate to be applied to those programmes should also be amended;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Poultrymeat and Eggs,
